{
  "text": "Proving termination of the TRS in Table 5 , modulo AC, is a complicated matter. This is mainly due to the presence of Rule 7, in which the left-hand side can be obtained from the right-hand side by the removal of subterms. A powerful technique for proving termination of TRSs that incorporate such rules is semantic labelling [CITATION_1] , where operation symbols that occur in the rewrite rules are supplied with labels, which depend on the semantics of the arguments. Then two TRSs are involved: the original system and the labelled system. The main theorem of [CITATION_2] states that the labelled system terminates if and only if the original system terminates.",
  "citation_candidates": [
